	     B. Allen  Lay
	     
	  



venture capitalist



		B. Allen Lay, American venture capitalist. Member of American Electronics Association  (board directors 1980-1982), American Management Association, Beta Gamma Sigma.
		
       		



Background




Lay, B. Allen was born on October 7, 1934 in Archie, Missouri, United States. Son of Robert Marvin and Florence Cathrine (Rittman) Lay.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor of Science in Business and Industrial Management, Kansas University, 1956.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			Manufacturing manager Computer Products Division Ampex Corporation, Los Angeles, 1959—1966. Materials manager Computer Measurements Company, 1966—1967. Vice president, operations manager Pertec Computer Corporation, 1967—1974, senior  vice president, group officer data system group, 1975—1979.President chief operating officer, director Cado Systems, Torrance, California, 1979—1982. General partner Southern California Ventures, Inglewood, since 1983. Director Interactive Machines Inc., Westlake, Precision Image Inc., Redwood City, Speech Systems Inc., Los Angeles, Dayflo Inc., Irvine, Federal Reserve System Inc., Sacramento.Served to major United States Marine Corps, 1956-1959.
			
       			












Politics


Party affiliation:
Republican




Religion


Denomination:
Presbyterian




Membership


			Member of American Electronics Association  (board directors 1980-1982), American Management Association, Beta Gamma Sigma.
			
    			







Connections


			Married Dorothy Valeria Rossel Lay, June 6, 1956. Children: John Robert, Katherine Marie.
			
    			



father:

					
                            Robert Marvin Lay
                        
				







